{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3.5 Technologies And Methods\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The implementation uses Python, pandas, scikit-learn, and Streamlit (Scikit-learn, 2019). The main modules are:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 src/edu_recommender/data.py} for loading structured project data\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 src/edu_recommender/text.py} for text processing helpers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 src/edu_recommender/models.py} for scoring and recommendation models\par}
