{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3.7 Testing And Evaluation Plan\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The evaluation compares the popularity baseline, content-based recommender, and hybrid recommender on seven sample learner profiles. Prototype relevance judgements mark resources that directly address a learner\u8217's target pathway and weak areas. The main ranking metrics are Precision@K, Recall@K, and NDCG@K, with K=5 because the learner-facing use case emphasizes a short ranked list rather than a long catalogue. The metric formulas are listed in Appendix C.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The prototype will also be tested through functional checks:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab app loads successfully\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab both Learner View and Research View work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab sample and custom profiles work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab each path stage has content\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab checking a resource does not reorder recommendations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab reset clears progress\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Research View remains readable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab pipeline still runs\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The evaluation results will be interpreted as prototype evidence rather than large-scale proof of learning outcomes. The current labels are curated and should be strengthened later with learner or supervisor feedback.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Chapter 4: Feature Prototype\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The feature prototype implements one of the most important technical features of the project: an explainable staged learning path generated from career-aware recommendations. It is implemented as a Streamlit app in {\f1 src/app.py}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The prototype has two views. The Learner View allows a sample learner profile or a custom learner profile to be selected. It shows profile details, skill gaps, a staged path, recommendation reasons, resource metadata, completed-resource checkboxes, and simple skill increases such as {\f1 SQL 1 > 2}. The Research View shows ranked outputs and model comparison metrics for the FYP evaluation. Prototype screenshots are included in Appendix D.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The staged path has four sections:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\f1 Learn just enough}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\f1 Start a practical project}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\f1 Deepen later}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab {\f1 Optional structured tracks}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The design separates precise recommendations from broad tracks. Broad career tracks can still appear, but only as optional structured references. This keeps the project aligned with the goal of recommending \u8220"just enough\u8221" to begin practical work and then deepen later.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The current feature prototype also preserves the recommendation order while a learner marks resources as completed. Completed resources are marked visually, and reset clears progress. This behaviour is important because immediate reordering after each checkbox click could make the recommendation path feel unstable.\par}
